From: souliane <21343492+souliane@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 21 Jun 2026 17:16:02 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] test(provision): add per-step timeout guard with
 comprehensive test coverage

Wire a timeout guard (ProvisionTimeoutError) that applies per provision step,
preventing indefinite hangs during stalled operations (e.g. DB imports,
migrations). The guard is configurable via overlay
(provision_step_timeout_seconds, default 300s) and logs step name + timeout on
timeout. A stalling step is aborted with a clear error message naming both.

Acceptance criteria:
- Timeout applies per provision step (separate timeout for each step)
- Configurable via overlay and defaults to 300 seconds per step
- On timeout, emits clear error naming step + timeout value
- Unit test asserts timeout fires on a stalled step; passing steps complete
- Full test suite passes; coverage maintained

Co-Authored-By: Claude Haiku 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
