From: souliane <21343492+souliane@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 21 Jun 2026 15:40:01 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] refactor(provision): wire timeout guard to callable-based
 provision steps

Wire the signal-based timeout guard from provision.py into run_callable_step()
so that all callable-based provision steps (e.g., db_import, overlay
installations, migrations) are protected from indefinite hangs. When a callable
step exceeds the configured timeout, it raises ProvisionTimeoutError which is
caught and converted to a failed StepResult with a clear error message.

Add test coverage verifying that callable steps exceed timeout and complete
before timeout as expected.

Closes #TODO-7

Co-Authored-By: Claude Haiku 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
